This third argument begins with words almost identical with those used in 1. 551. The arguments are closely related. Hence Giussani places ll. 577-583 aster 1. 564. The reasons for transposition are strong; but so much here is uncertain that I leave the lines where they stand.

577. el has the sense of etsi: ‘even if’ we grant the infinite divisibility of matter. 578. quaeque...corpora=cuiqne rei sua corpora.
